<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002578.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Clubber Lang</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">  Man what is this?  Is it just me or is it that evertime I am battling a blue mob or up it starts to fight twice as hard once I have 3/4 of its health down?<BR> <BR>It seems to happen to me everytime I solo, I might be destroying the mob pretty well then all of a sudden once its health gets to about 1/3 it will start hitting me BIG and I will start missing big.  all of a sudden I am about in low in health as the MOB.  <P>So what kinda feature is this?  Do MOBs go into a berzerker frenzy when low on health?  They seem to get a Attack and AC bonus for some reason.  <P>Not only that, but they get that big hit sound while they are wailing huge blows on ya.  You know, the sound that you get when you make a BIG hit (similar to that of when you hit a mummy).<P>So whats the deal with this?  Makes soloing mobs twice as difficult.  Damn I wish my berzerker frenzy's would be this battle effective, would help me turn the tide in battle.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Brudo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Warrior-type mobs have had this ever since warriors got it; mobs share PC abilities and spells to an extent, so (for instance) when necros lost charm, Meldrath could no longer do it.<P>It's not all mobs, though, just warriors. In general, it's pretty obvious which ones the warriors are, but if you want an exact list, go through the ShowEQ lists and look at the mob types. All 'warrior' mobs will be of the same type.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Lasae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Wait...I've never seen a mob get a critical hit on me before...oh wait, if you can punch for 119 damage, and a fish can kick...yeah...they don't *need* criticals...<P>------------------<BR>Lasae Leniyersa<BR>Vallon Zek<BR>Emerald Warriorette of the 44th Season <BR><I>Master Fletcher: 192</I><BR><I>Average Archery Skill: 64</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Brudo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Actually, when crits were first put in on test, all mobs could crit for a couple of days  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"> Ask a test server player about that sometime...not fun.<P>Brudo (E'ci)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Martigahn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I must admit I kinda experienced such thing: mob low health hits harder (when it does not flee frightenned by my XXXXtreme power  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/biggrin.gif"> ). They don't crit hit of course but I am under impression they are more likely to hit for full damage ....<P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
